    "causal_summary": "The five mcp-* skills had drifted out of a shared shape. mcp-figma was still labelled pre-1.0 (`0.1.0`) even though its CLI was live-verified and an embedded install scaffold was added. mcp-open-design had no INSTALL_GUIDE and no `scripts/` at all, so it could not be installed or diagnosed like its siblings. mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-click-up had an `install.sh` but no read-only `doctor.sh`. The central `/doctor:mcp` command knew only the registered MCP servers, so the CLI-primary design skills were invisible to it. Finally, the three design skills (mcp-figma, mcp-open-design, sk-interface-design) referenced each other only partially.",
